OL,3,COne of the UK's oldest Hospice's
OL,4,Ccelebrates its 50th birthday
OL,6,FMel Barham spoke to staff and families
OL,7,Fat St Joseph's Hospice means to them,
OL,8,Fand why they say it needs to survive.
OL,10,FOne of the oldest hospices in the
OL,11,Fcountry has been celebrating its 50th
OL,12,Fanniversary, but warns it needs more
OL,13,Ffunding to keep up its important work.
OL,15,FSt Joseph's Hospice in Thornton, , has
OL,16,Fcared for thousands of local people as
OL,17,Fthey approached the end of their lives
OL,18,Fsince it first opened on 19 March 1974.
