OL,4,Ccelebrates its 50th birthday
OL,6,F"If you look at the mathematics, we
OL,7,Fare much cheaper than a hospital stay.
OL,8,FI would never want to be 100% funded
OL,9,Fby the NHS but we do need an uplift in
OL,10,Ffunding."
OL,12,FDespite the tough conditions, Mike
OL,13,Fremains confident the hospice will
OL,14,Fsurvive to celebrate its 100th
OL,15,Fbirthday in 50 years time.
OL,17,FHe said: "Right now, arguably it's
OL,18,Fharder than ever... but if we look at
OL,19,Fwhere we started in 1974, (our
OL,20,Ffounder) faced a huge challenge
OL,21,Fopening the doors for the first time."
