OL,3,COne of the UK's oldest Hospice's
OL,4,Ccelebrates its 50th birthday
OL,6,FLocal member of the community Father
OL,7,FFrancis O'Leary purchased what was
OL,8,Fthen called Thornton Manor in 1972. It
OL,9,Ftook him two years to raise enough
OL,10,Fmoney to reopen the building as St
OL,11,FJoseph's Hospice.
OL,13,FMike said: "The economic situation
OL,14,Fmakes it harder for people to donate,
OL,15,Fbut we do have fantastic support from
OL,16,Four community and I have to assume
OL,17,Fthat's because of the service we
OL,18,Fprovide.
